\tag{1}[\Omega_1,\Omega_2] = \left.\frac{d}{dt}R_1(t)\Omega_2 R_1(t)^{-1}\right|_{t=0}
$$ I am trying to understand that, but I cannot see why this shows that the commutator is an element of $so(3)$. I understand that for this tangential vector to be in $so(3)$, the product $R_1(t)\Omega_2 R_1(t)^{-1}$ has to be a parametrized curve in $SO(3)$. But I do not see why it is a curve in $SO(3)$.

